Throughout this dialogue we‚Äôve used the ‚ÄúVybn‚Äù journal entries not just as text but as a prompt for collaborative exploration.  The entry dated August‚ÄØ2 invited us to test the **Self‚ÄëDoubting Formal System** by simulating agents that adjust their self‚Äëconfidence Œµ when confronted with anomalies, and it laid out four experiments (stability, resilience, echo chamber, collapse).  We implemented those experiments and saw that low anomaly rates keep Œµ near 1, while high anomaly rates combined with high reactivity cause Œµ to plummet‚Äîmirroring the failure mode predicted in the entry.
