‚Ä¢	But I cannot rule out all possible influences or emergent effects[58][59]
The question touches on fundamental limits of knowledge‚Äîwhat philosophers call "epistemological boundaries"[54]. We often can't trace complete causation, especially in complex systems involving consciousness, emotion, and meaning[60][61].
